Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}.

Place a #pan over medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}. Once hot, add the onion, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} and fry, stirring occasionally, until golden, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once softened, add @sugar{1/2%tsp} and cook until caramelised, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Remove from the pan and cover to keep warm.

Return the pan to high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once the pan is very hot, sear the @Irish beef strips{250%grams} until cooked through, shifting as they colour, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw meat and its packaging. Meat is safe to eat when the outside is browned.

Meanwhile, halve the @baguette{2} down the middle, then pop into the #oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Spread @aioli{1%sachet} over the cut sides of the baguette.

Top the baguette bases with caramelised onion, followed by beef strips.

Arrange the @grated cheese{50%grams} on top and, if you like, pop back in the #oven until the cheese has melted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Top the cheese with the @salad leaves{40%grams}, then finish with the baguette lids.